{
  "name": "Rush To The Head",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/blood.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When using a blood art that allows a Fortitude save, you may replace all Fortitude saves that effect allows for with Will saves.</p>\n<p>In addition, as a standard action, you rush the target&#8217;s blood to their head and away from their vital organs, disorienting them. On a failed Fortitude save, the target suffers blood loss and falls prone. If you spend an additional spell point when casting this effect, the target also becomes confused for 1 round per caster level. While confused by this effect, whenever the target rolls to determine behavior in a given round, add twice the blood loss to the result (maximum 100).</p>\n",
